  "description": "Bounded promotion proof for string_abi numeric conversion aliases, GNU argz/envz helpers, globfree release, and old GNU regex entrypoints whose implementations are native Rust ABI adaptation with expected errno and allocator bridge reachability.",
  "rationale": "The __strto* rows forward into FrankenLibC stdlib conversion entrypoints, the argz/envz rows rebuild owned buffers through FrankenLibC allocation helpers, globfree releases FrankenLibC-owned glob vectors, and the re_* rows execute the native regex core while optionally allocating legacy register storage. Host-delegation census hits are bootstrap, errno, allocator, or intra-module compatibility helpers, not direct semantic call-through for the promoted string API bodies.",
